list.name: Changes
list.comment:
Introduced paste_to_sheet() function which can take either .xlsx or .csv files and paste them into a sheet. Previously this needed to be done with two functions for .xlsx files open_vals_only_sheet() and paste_sheet_to_sheet(), with the second also requiring the desired number of columns to be specified. paste_csv_vals_to_sheet() had to be used in the event that it was a .csv file. Now columns and file type do not need to be determined in advance.
get_file_path() now checks if it is a compatible file (xlsx or csv) and deletes it and informs the user if it is a .json file, and leaves it but notifies the user if it is a fourth file type.
count_columns(ws) sub function introduced so that columns don't need to be specified when pasting in an .xlsx sheet
